Note: ===================================================================
Note: HCL TO HIR TRANSLATOR
Note: ===================================================================
Note: Translates HCL Abstract Syntax Tree to Runa HIR (High-level
Note: Intermediate Representation) for universal language translation.

Note: Part of the Translation Translation System
Note: Location: compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/frontends/hcl/hcl_to_hir.runa
Note: ===================================================================

Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/hir_nodes.runa" as HIR
Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/frontends/hcl/hcl_parser.runa" as HCLParser
Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/frontends/hcl/hcl_lexer.runa" as HCLLexer
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa" as StringCore
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_primitive.runa" as StringPrim
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/list.runa" as ListCore
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/dictionary.runa" as DictCore

Note: ===================================================================
Note: TRANSLATION CONTEXT
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
HCL translation is block-scoped (resources, modules, variables, locals all introduce nested namespaces), so the translator needs a mutable context that grows and shrinks as blocks are entered. Bundling hir_module, current_scope, block_stack, and a metadata dictionary into one record lets every translator function take a single ctx parameter.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Four integer slots: hir_module is the root module being built, current_scope is the currently active HIR scope (set by block translators), block_stack tracks nested HCL block ancestry, and metadata stores translator-wide flags used by helpers like splat and for-expr.
@End Implementation

Type called "HCLTranslationContext":
    hir_module as Integer
    current_scope as Integer
    block_stack as Integer
    metadata as Integer
End Type

@Reasoning:
Constructor seeded with a fresh HIR module named "hcl_config" because every HCL file produces exactly one logical configuration root. Empty block_stack and metadata are initialised eagerly so subsequent translators never have to null-check them.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Allocates an HCLTranslationContext value, calls HIR.hir_create_module with the literal "hcl_config" name, sets current_scope to 0 (top-level), and primes block_stack via list_create and metadata via dict_create.
@End Implementation

Process called "create_translation_context" returns Integer:
    Let hir_module be proc hir_create_module from HIR
    proc hir_set_module_name from HIR with hir_module, "hcl_config"

    Let ctx be a value of type HCLTranslationContext with
        hir_module as hir_module,
        current_scope as 0,
        block_stack as proc list_create from ListCore,
        metadata as proc create from DictCore

    Return ctx
End Process

Note: ===================================================================
Note: MAIN TRANSLATION ENTRY POINT
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
Single entry point that owns the lifetime of the translation context. Returning ctx.hir_module after translation surfaces only the result, hiding the transient block stack and metadata used during translation.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Creates a fresh context, walks the AST top-level via translate_configuration, then returns the populated hir_module field from ctx.
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_hcl_to_hir" takes hcl_ast as Integer returns Integer:
    Let ctx be proc create_translation_context

    Note: Translate top-level configuration
    proc translate_configuration with ctx, hcl_ast

    Return ctx.hir_module
End Process

Note: ===================================================================
Note: CONFIGURATION TRANSLATION
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
The top-level of an HCL document is a flat sequence of either blocks (resource, variable, output, module, provider, data, locals, terraform, dynamic) or bare attributes. Dispatching by HCL_* tag keeps each block flavour translated by its dedicated routine that knows the exact label and body shape for that flavour.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Iterates AST children of config_node, reads each child's node type, and forwards to the matching block translator. Bare attributes at the top level go through translate_attribute. Unknown tags are silently dropped which keeps the translator robust to future HCL extensions.
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_configuration" takes ctx as Integer, config_node as Integer:
    Let child_count be proc ast_node_child_count from HCLParser with config_node
    Let i be 0

    While i is less than child_count:
        Let child be proc ast_node_child from HCLParser with config_node, i
        Let child_type be proc ast_node_type from HCLParser with child

        Note: Translate blocks
        If child_type is equal to HCLParser.HCL_RESOURCE_BLOCK:
            proc translate_resource_block with ctx, child
        End If

        If child_type is equal to HCLParser.HCL_VARIABLE_BLOCK:
            proc translate_variable_block with ctx, child
        End If

        If child_type is equal to HCLParser.HCL_OUTPUT_BLOCK:
            proc translate_output_block with ctx, child
        End If

        If child_type is equal to HCLParser.HCL_MODULE_BLOCK:
            proc translate_module_block with ctx, child
        End If

        If child_type is equal to HCLParser.HCL_PROVIDER_BLOCK:
            proc translate_provider_block with ctx, child
        End If

        If child_type is equal to HCLParser.HCL_DATA_BLOCK:
            proc translate_data_block with ctx, child
        End If

        If child_type is equal to HCLParser.HCL_LOCALS_BLOCK:
            proc translate_locals_block with ctx, child
        End If

        If child_type is equal to HCLParser.HCL_TERRAFORM_BLOCK:
            proc translate_terraform_block with ctx, child
        End If

        If child_type is equal to HCLParser.HCL_DYNAMIC_BLOCK:
            proc translate_dynamic_block with ctx, child
        End If

        If child_type is equal to HCLParser.HCL_ATTRIBUTE:
            proc translate_attribute with ctx, child
        End If

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
End Process

Note: ===================================================================
Note: BLOCK TRANSLATION
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
A Terraform/HCL resource carries two string labels (provider type and instance name) before its body. The translator concatenates these into a single HIR class name and stamps both labels as metadata so downstream tooling can recover the original identity.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Walks block_node children, treating leading HCL_LITERAL children as labels until a non-literal child stops the label phase (the loop sets i to 999999 as a break sentinel). Concatenates type and name with an underscore for the HIR class name, attaches metadata, then forwards remaining children to translate_block_body_item under the new class. Finally registers the class on ctx.hir_module.
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_resource_block" takes ctx as Integer, block_node as Integer:
    Note: resource "type" "name" { ... }
    Let block_name be proc ast_node_value from HCLParser with block_node

    Note: Get labels (type and name)
    Let child_count be proc ast_node_child_count from HCLParser with block_node
    Let labels be proc list_create from ListCore
    Let i be 0

    Note: Extract labels (first children are labels)
    While i is less than child_count:
        Let child be proc ast_node_child from HCLParser with block_node, i
        Let child_type be proc ast_node_type from HCLParser with child

        If child_type is equal to HCLParser.HCL_LITERAL:
            Let label_value be proc ast_node_value from HCLParser with child
            proc list_append from ListCore with labels, label_value
            Set i to i plus 1
        Otherwise:
            Note: No more labels, break
            Set i to 999999
        End If
    End While

    Note: Create HIR class to represent resource
    Let resource_type be ""
    Let resource_name be ""

    Let label_count be proc list_length from ListCore with labels
    If label_count is greater than 0:
        Set resource_type to proc list_get from ListCore with labels, 0
    End If
    If label_count is greater than 1:
        Set resource_name to proc list_get from ListCore with labels, 1
    End If

    Let class_name be proc string_concat from StringPrim with resource_type, "_"
    Set class_name to proc string_concat from StringPrim with class_name, resource_name

    Let hir_class be proc hir_create_class from HIR
    proc hir_set_class_name from HIR with hir_class, class_name

    Note: Mark as HCL resource
    proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_class, "hcl_block_type", "resource"
    proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_class, "hcl_resource_type", resource_type
    proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_class, "hcl_resource_name", resource_name

    Note: Translate block body (attributes and nested blocks)
    Set i to label_count
    While i is less than child_count:
        Set child to proc ast_node_child from HCLParser with block_node, i
        proc translate_block_body_item with ctx, child, hir_class
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Note: Add class to module
    proc hir_add_declaration from HIR with ctx.hir_module, hir_class
End Process

@Reasoning:
An HCL variable block declares a typed parameter with optional default, type, and description attributes. It maps cleanly to a single HIR variable record whose attributes survive as metadata so the eventual emitter can reproduce or query them.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads the single label as variable name, creates a HIR variable of HIR_TYPE_ANY, then iterates children from index 1 onward looking for HCL_ATTRIBUTE entries. For each attribute, stores the first child expression as metadata keyed by the attribute name.
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_variable_block" takes ctx as Integer, block_node as Integer:
    Note: variable "name" { ... }
    Let child_count be proc ast_node_child_count from HCLParser with block_node
    Let var_name be ""

    Note: Get variable name (first label)
    If child_count is greater than 0:
        Let label_child be proc ast_node_child from HCLParser with block_node, 0
        Let label_type be proc ast_node_type from HCLParser with label_child
        If label_type is equal to HCLParser.HCL_LITERAL:
            Set var_name to proc ast_node_value from HCLParser with label_child
        End If
    End If

    Note: Represent every HCL block uniformly as a HIR class so the backend reads block bodies
    Note: through a single class-member path. The single label is preserved as metadata.
    Let hir_var be proc hir_create_class from HIR
    proc hir_set_class_name from HIR with hir_var, var_name
    proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_var, "hcl_block_type", "variable"
    proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_var, "hcl_label_0", var_name

    Note: Process variable attributes (type, default, description) as class fields
    Let i be 1
    While i is less than child_count:
        Let child be proc ast_node_child from HCLParser with block_node, i
        proc translate_block_body_item with ctx, child, hir_var
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Note: Add to module
    proc hir_add_declaration from HIR with ctx.hir_module, hir_var
End Process

@Reasoning:
HCL output blocks publish a value computed from other resources. The translator records them as HIR constants — the value is set by the "value" attribute discovered during body iteration via translate_block_body_item.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Captures the single output name label, creates a HIR constant with HIR_TYPE_ANY and initial value 0, marks it with "hcl_block_type"="output" metadata, then forwards each remaining child to translate_block_body_item so any attributes (value, description, sensitive) become HIR fields on the constant.
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_output_block" takes ctx as Integer, block_node as Integer:
    Note: output "name" { value = ... }
    Let child_count be proc ast_node_child_count from HCLParser with block_node
    Let output_name be ""

    Note: Get output name
    If child_count is greater than 0:
        Let label_child be proc ast_node_child from HCLParser with block_node, 0
        Let label_type be proc ast_node_type from HCLParser with label_child
        If label_type is equal to HCLParser.HCL_LITERAL:
            Set output_name to proc ast_node_value from HCLParser with label_child
        End If
    End If

    Note: Represent the output block as a HIR class (uniform with all block kinds) so the
    Note: backend regenerates it through the shared class-member body path.
    Let hir_output be proc hir_create_class from HIR
    proc hir_set_class_name from HIR with hir_output, output_name
    proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_output, "hcl_block_type", "output"
    proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_output, "hcl_label_0", output_name

    Note: Process output attributes
    Let i be 1
    While i is less than child_count:
        Let child be proc ast_node_child from HCLParser with block_node, i
        proc translate_block_body_item with ctx, child, hir_output
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Note: Add to module
    proc hir_add_declaration from HIR with ctx.hir_module, hir_output
End Process

@Reasoning:
Module blocks in HCL load and parameterise external modules. Modeling them as HIR classes preserves the namespacing of their inputs (each attribute is a field). The single label gives the local module instance name.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads the module instance name from the first label child, creates an HIR class with that name, stamps "hcl_block_type" and "hcl_module_name" metadata, then iterates children from index 1 and forwards each to translate_block_body_item which adds attributes/nested blocks as members.
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_module_block" takes ctx as Integer, block_node as Integer:
    Note: module "name" { source = "..." }
    Let child_count be proc ast_node_child_count from HCLParser with block_node
    Let module_name be ""

    If child_count is greater than 0:
        Let label_child be proc ast_node_child from HCLParser with block_node, 0
        Let label_type be proc ast_node_type from HCLParser with label_child
        If label_type is equal to HCLParser.HCL_LITERAL:
            Set module_name to proc ast_node_value from HCLParser with label_child
        End If
    End If

    Note: Create HIR class to represent module
    Let hir_class be proc hir_create_class from HIR
    proc hir_set_class_name from HIR with hir_class, module_name

    proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_class, "hcl_block_type", "module"
    proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_class, "hcl_module_name", module_name

    Let i be 1
    While i is less than child_count:
        Let child be proc ast_node_child from HCLParser with block_node, i
        proc translate_block_body_item with ctx, child, hir_class
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    proc hir_add_declaration from HIR with ctx.hir_module, hir_class
End Process

@Reasoning:
Provider configuration blocks describe Terraform provider plugins. Like module blocks they have one name label and a body of attributes; the body shape is provider-specific so the translator simply preserves attributes as class members rather than imposing schema.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Extracts the provider name from the first label child, creates an HIR class named after the provider, stamps "hcl_block_type" and "hcl_provider_name" metadata, then walks children from index 1 through translate_block_body_item which converts attributes to HIR fields.
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_provider_block" takes ctx as Integer, block_node as Integer:
    Note: provider "name" { ... }
    Let child_count be proc ast_node_child_count from HCLParser with block_node
    Let provider_name be ""

    If child_count is greater than 0:
        Let label_child be proc ast_node_child from HCLParser with block_node, 0
        Let label_type be proc ast_node_type from HCLParser with label_child
        If label_type is equal to HCLParser.HCL_LITERAL:
            Set provider_name to proc ast_node_value from HCLParser with label_child
        End If
    End If

    Let hir_class be proc hir_create_class from HIR
    proc hir_set_class_name from HIR with hir_class, provider_name

    proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_class, "hcl_block_type", "provider"
    proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_class, "hcl_provider_name", provider_name

    Let i be 1
    While i is less than child_count:
        Let child be proc ast_node_child from HCLParser with block_node, i
        proc translate_block_body_item with ctx, child, hir_class
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    proc hir_add_declaration from HIR with ctx.hir_module, hir_class
End Process

@Reasoning:
Data sources have the same two-label shape as resources (type and name) but are read-only lookups rather than managed resources. The translator distinguishes them by prefixing the HIR class name with "data_" and tagging "hcl_block_type"="data" so downstream code can split create-vs-read concerns.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Mirrors translate_resource_block's two-label loop, breaking out by setting the index past child_count once a non-literal child appears. Builds an HIR class with name "data_<type>_<name>", stamps three metadata keys, then forwards remaining children to translate_block_body_item.
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_data_block" takes ctx as Integer, block_node as Integer:
    Note: data "type" "name" { ... }
    Let child_count be proc ast_node_child_count from HCLParser with block_node
    Let labels be proc list_create from ListCore
    Let i be 0

    While i is less than child_count:
        Let child be proc ast_node_child from HCLParser with block_node, i
        Let child_type be proc ast_node_type from HCLParser with child

        If child_type is equal to HCLParser.HCL_LITERAL:
            Let label_value be proc ast_node_value from HCLParser with child
            proc list_append from ListCore with labels, label_value
            Set i to i plus 1
        Otherwise:
            Set i to 999999
        End If
    End While

    Let data_type be ""
    Let data_name be ""
    Let label_count be proc list_length from ListCore with labels

    If label_count is greater than 0:
        Set data_type to proc list_get from ListCore with labels, 0
    End If
    If label_count is greater than 1:
        Set data_name to proc list_get from ListCore with labels, 1
    End If

    Let class_name be proc string_concat from StringPrim with "data_", data_type
    Set class_name to proc string_concat from StringPrim with class_name, "_"
    Set class_name to proc string_concat from StringPrim with class_name, data_name

    Let hir_class be proc hir_create_class from HIR
    proc hir_set_class_name from HIR with hir_class, class_name

    proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_class, "hcl_block_type", "data"
    proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_class, "hcl_data_type", data_type
    proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_class, "hcl_data_name", data_name

    Set i to label_count
    While i is less than child_count:
        Set child to proc ast_node_child from HCLParser with block_node, i
        proc translate_block_body_item with ctx, child, hir_class
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    proc hir_add_declaration from HIR with ctx.hir_module, hir_class
End Process

@Reasoning:
A locals block declares multiple named local values in one HCL block. Rather than creating a single HIR aggregate, the translator promotes each attribute to its own top-level HIR constant tagged "hcl_local" so each local is independently addressable from later expressions.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Iterates the block's children; for each HCL_ATTRIBUTE child, creates a fresh HIR constant named after the attribute, translates the attribute's first child expression to HIR, sets that as the constant's value, and registers the constant on ctx.hir_module.
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_locals_block" takes ctx as Integer, block_node as Integer:
    Note: locals { ... }
    Let child_count be proc ast_node_child_count from HCLParser with block_node
    Let i be 0

    While i is less than child_count:
        Let child be proc ast_node_child from HCLParser with block_node, i
        Let child_type be proc ast_node_type from HCLParser with child

        If child_type is equal to HCLParser.HCL_ATTRIBUTE:
            Let attr_name be proc ast_node_value from HCLParser with child
            Let hir_const be proc hir_create_variable from HIR
            proc hir_set_variable_name from HIR with hir_const, attr_name
            proc hir_set_variable_type from HIR with hir_const, HIR.HIR_TYPE_ANY
            proc hir_set_variable_const from HIR with hir_const, 1

            proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_const, "hcl_local", 1

            Let attr_child_count be proc ast_node_child_count from HCLParser with child
            If attr_child_count is greater than 0:
                Let value_expr be proc ast_node_child from HCLParser with child, 0
                Let hir_value be proc translate_expression with ctx, value_expr
                proc hir_set_variable_initializer from HIR with hir_const, hir_value
            End If

            proc hir_add_declaration from HIR with ctx.hir_module, hir_const
        End If

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
End Process

@Reasoning:
The terraform settings block is a single labelless block whose attributes (required_version, backend, etc.) configure tooling rather than infrastructure. Translating it as a HIR class named "terraform_config" gives it a stable identity for emitters.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Creates the HIR class with the fixed name "terraform_config", stamps "hcl_block_type"="terraform" metadata, then forwards every child to translate_block_body_item starting from index 0 (no label children to skip).
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_terraform_block" takes ctx as Integer, block_node as Integer:
    Note: terraform { required_version = "..." }
    Let hir_class be proc hir_create_class from HIR
    proc hir_set_class_name from HIR with hir_class, "terraform_config"

    proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_class, "hcl_block_type", "terraform"

    Let child_count be proc ast_node_child_count from HCLParser with block_node
    Let i be 0

    While i is less than child_count:
        Let child be proc ast_node_child from HCLParser with block_node, i
        proc translate_block_body_item with ctx, child, hir_class
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    proc hir_add_declaration from HIR with ctx.hir_module, hir_class
End Process

@Reasoning:
Dynamic blocks expand at runtime over for_each iterations. The translator preserves them as HIR classes named after the dynamic block's label, with metadata identifying them as dynamic so a later HIR pass can implement the expansion semantics.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads the block name from the first label, creates an HIR class with that name, stamps "hcl_block_type"="dynamic" and "hcl_dynamic_block"=<name> metadata, then forwards remaining children (for_each, iterator, labels, content) to translate_block_body_item.
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_dynamic_block" takes ctx as Integer, block_node as Integer:
    Note: dynamic "block_name" { for_each = ... content { ... } }
    Let child_count be proc ast_node_child_count from HCLParser with block_node
    Let block_name be ""

    If child_count is greater than 0:
        Let label_child be proc ast_node_child from HCLParser with block_node, 0
        Let label_type be proc ast_node_type from HCLParser with label_child
        If label_type is equal to HCLParser.HCL_LITERAL:
            Set block_name to proc ast_node_value from HCLParser with label_child
        End If
    End If

    Let hir_class be proc hir_create_class from HIR
    proc hir_set_class_name from HIR with hir_class, block_name

    proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_class, "hcl_block_type", "dynamic"
    proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_class, "hcl_dynamic_block", block_name

    Let i be 1
    While i is less than child_count:
        Let child be proc ast_node_child from HCLParser with block_node, i
        proc translate_block_body_item with ctx, child, hir_class
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    proc hir_add_declaration from HIR with ctx.hir_module, hir_class
End Process

@Reasoning:
Shared helper used by every block translator to convert one body item into an HIR member of the surrounding class. Centralising attribute-vs-nested-block dispatch keeps each block translator from duplicating the same six lines of If/Otherwise glue.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
For HCL_ATTRIBUTE items: extracts the attribute name and translates its first child expression to HIR, wraps the result as a HIR field with initializer, and adds it as a member of parent_hir. For nested HCL_RESOURCE_BLOCK or HCL_DYNAMIC_BLOCK items, defers to the corresponding block translator so they appear as siblings on the module rather than being misnested.
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_block_body_item" takes ctx as Integer, item_node as Integer, parent_hir as Integer:
    Let item_type be proc ast_node_type from HCLParser with item_node

    If item_type is equal to HCLParser.HCL_ATTRIBUTE:
        Let attr_name be proc ast_node_value from HCLParser with item_node
        Let child_count be proc ast_node_child_count from HCLParser with item_node

        If child_count is greater than 0:
            Let value_expr be proc ast_node_child from HCLParser with item_node, 0
            Let hir_value be proc translate_expression with ctx, value_expr

            Note: Create HIR field
            Let hir_field be proc hir_create_field from HIR
            proc hir_set_field_name from HIR with hir_field, attr_name
            proc hir_set_field_type from HIR with hir_field, HIR.HIR_TYPE_ANY
            proc hir_set_field_initializer from HIR with hir_field, hir_value
            proc hir_add_class_member from HIR with parent_hir, hir_field
        End If
    End If

    Note: Generic nested block (network { ... }, lifecycle { ... }, etc.). The block keyword is
    Note: stored in the node value; we materialise it as a nested HIR class carrying
    Note: hcl_block_type="nested" and hcl_nested_name=<keyword> metadata, then recurse over its
    Note: body so attributes and deeper nested blocks become members of THIS nested class. The
    Note: nested class is attached as a member of the surrounding block (parent_hir).
    If item_type is equal to HCLParser.HCL_BLOCK:
        Let nested_keyword be proc ast_node_value from HCLParser with item_node
        Let nested_class be proc hir_create_class from HIR
        proc hir_set_class_name from HIR with nested_class, nested_keyword
        proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with nested_class, "hcl_block_type", "nested"
        proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with nested_class, "hcl_nested_name", nested_keyword

        Let nested_child_count be proc ast_node_child_count from HCLParser with item_node
        Let n be 0
        While n is less than nested_child_count:
            Let nested_child be proc ast_node_child from HCLParser with item_node, n
            proc translate_block_body_item with ctx, nested_child, nested_class
            Set n to n plus 1
        End While

        proc hir_add_class_member from HIR with parent_hir, nested_class
    End If

    Note: Nested resource/dynamic blocks keep their dedicated lowering (they register on the
    Note: module as the original translators intend).
    If item_type is equal to HCLParser.HCL_RESOURCE_BLOCK:
        proc translate_resource_block with ctx, item_node
    End If

    If item_type is equal to HCLParser.HCL_DYNAMIC_BLOCK:
        proc translate_dynamic_block with ctx, item_node
    End If
End Process

@Reasoning:
A bare attribute at the top level of an HCL file (outside any block) is treated as a module-level constant. This handles legacy HCL where settings could appear at file scope.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads the attribute name from the AST node, translates its first child expression to HIR, then creates an HIR constant initialised with that value and registers it on ctx.hir_module.
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_attribute" takes ctx as Integer, attr_node as Integer:
    Let attr_name be proc ast_node_value from HCLParser with attr_node
    Let child_count be proc ast_node_child_count from HCLParser with attr_node

    If child_count is greater than 0:
        Let value_expr be proc ast_node_child from HCLParser with attr_node, 0
        Let hir_value be proc translate_expression with ctx, value_expr

        Let hir_const be proc hir_create_variable from HIR
        proc hir_set_variable_name from HIR with hir_const, attr_name
        proc hir_set_variable_type from HIR with hir_const, HIR.HIR_TYPE_ANY
        proc hir_set_variable_const from HIR with hir_const, 1
        proc hir_set_variable_initializer from HIR with hir_const, hir_value
        proc hir_add_declaration from HIR with ctx.hir_module, hir_const
    End If
End Process

Note: ===================================================================
Note: EXPRESSION TRANSLATION
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
HCL expression grammar covers 12 distinct node types (literals, identifiers, collections, operators, conditionals, calls, member/index access, splat, for-comprehensions). A flat dispatch by node-type tag keeps each variant's translator independently testable.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads the expression's tag and forwards to the corresponding translate_* helper. Returns 0 for unknown tags, which propagates as an HIR null sentinel and lets the surrounding statement decide whether to fail or skip.
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_expression" takes ctx as Integer, expr_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let expr_type be proc ast_node_type from HCLParser with expr_node

    If expr_type is equal to HCLParser.HCL_LITERAL:
        Return proc translate_literal with ctx, expr_node
    End If

    If expr_type is equal to HCLParser.HCL_IDENTIFIER:
        Return proc translate_identifier with ctx, expr_node
    End If

    If expr_type is equal to HCLParser.HCL_LIST:
        Return proc translate_list with ctx, expr_node
    End If

    If expr_type is equal to HCLParser.HCL_MAP:
        Return proc translate_map with ctx, expr_node
    End If

    If expr_type is equal to HCLParser.HCL_OBJECT:
        Return proc translate_object with ctx, expr_node
    End If

    If expr_type is equal to HCLParser.HCL_BINARY_EXPR:
        Return proc translate_binary_expr with ctx, expr_node
    End If

    If expr_type is equal to HCLParser.HCL_UNARY_EXPR:
        Return proc translate_unary_expr with ctx, expr_node
    End If

    If expr_type is equal to HCLParser.HCL_CONDITIONAL:
        Return proc translate_conditional with ctx, expr_node
    End If

    If expr_type is equal to HCLParser.HCL_FUNCTION_CALL:
        Return proc translate_function_call with ctx, expr_node
    End If

    If expr_type is equal to HCLParser.HCL_MEMBER_EXPR:
        Return proc translate_member_expr with ctx, expr_node
    End If

    If expr_type is equal to HCLParser.HCL_INDEX_EXPR:
        Return proc translate_index_expr with ctx, expr_node
    End If

    If expr_type is equal to HCLParser.HCL_SPLAT_EXPR:
        Return proc translate_splat_expr with ctx, expr_node
    End If

    If expr_type is equal to HCLParser.HCL_FOR_EXPR:
        Return proc translate_for_expr with ctx, expr_node
    End If

    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
HCL literals are textually polymorphic — "true"/"false"/"null"/digits/quoted strings all surface as HCL_LITERAL with a string value. The translator must reclassify them so HIR sees Boolean, Null, Number, or String as distinct variants.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Tests value against the keywords "true", "false", "null" (using string_equals) in turn, emitting hir_create_boolean_literal/null_literal as appropriate. Otherwise reads the first byte; if it is an ASCII digit (48-57) emits hir_create_number_literal, else falls through to hir_create_string_literal.
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_literal" takes ctx as Integer, literal_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let value be proc ast_node_value from HCLParser with literal_node

    Note: Determine literal type
    Let is_true be proc string_equals from StringCore with value, "true"
    If is_true is equal to 1:
        Return proc hir_create_bool_literal from HIR with 1
    End If

    Let is_false be proc string_equals from StringCore with value, "false"
    If is_false is equal to 1:
        Return proc hir_create_bool_literal from HIR with 0
    End If

    Let is_null be proc string_equals from StringCore with value, "null"
    If is_null is equal to 1:
        Return proc hir_create_null_literal from HIR
    End If

    Note: Check if number. HCL numbers are textual (8080, 3.14, -1); we preserve the exact
    Note: source text by wrapping it in a HIR string literal tagged hcl_number so the backend
    Note: re-emits it unquoted without lossy integer/float parsing.
    Let first_char be proc string_char_at from StringCore with value, 0
    If first_char is greater than or equal to 48:
        If first_char is less than or equal to 57:
            Let hir_number be proc hir_create_string_literal from HIR with value
            proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_number, "hcl_number", 1
            Return hir_number
        End If
    End If

    Note: Otherwise string
    Return proc hir_create_string_literal from HIR with value
End Process

@Reasoning:
Identifier references in HCL flow directly to HIR identifiers with the same name; later semantic passes resolve them against the variable/local/resource scopes. No transformation is needed here.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads the identifier name from the AST node and forwards to hir_create_identifier.
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_identifier" takes ctx as Integer, ident_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let name be proc ast_node_value from HCLParser with ident_node
    Return proc hir_create_identifier from HIR with name
End Process

@Reasoning:
HCL list literals translate directly to HIR array literals; each element is itself an expression and must be recursively translated to preserve nested structure.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Creates an empty HIR array literal, iterates list_node children, translates each child through translate_expression, and appends the result via hir_add_array_element. Preserves order because the AST iterator yields children in source order.
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_list" takes ctx as Integer, list_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let hir_list be proc hir_create_list_literal from HIR

    Let child_count be proc ast_node_child_count from HCLParser with list_node
    Let i be 0

    While i is less than child_count:
        Let child be proc ast_node_child from HCLParser with list_node, i
        Let hir_elem be proc translate_expression with ctx, child
        proc hir_add_list_element from HIR with hir_list, hir_elem
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Return hir_list
End Process

@Reasoning:
HCL distinguishes maps from objects syntactically but they share the same HIR dictionary representation. Aliasing translate_map to translate_object avoids duplicating the conversion logic.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Single delegation to translate_object, passing the same context and node.
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_map" takes ctx as Integer, map_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc translate_object with ctx, map_node
End Process

@Reasoning:
HCL objects/maps map to HIR dictionary literals. Each child is an HCL_ATTRIBUTE; the attribute name becomes a string-literal key (HCL maps allow only string keys at this layer) and the attribute's first child expression becomes the value.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Creates an empty HIR dictionary literal, iterates obj_node children, processes only HCL_ATTRIBUTE entries (silently skipping anything else), translates the value expression, wraps the key as a string literal, and appends the pair via hir_add_dictionary_pair.
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_object" takes ctx as Integer, obj_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let hir_object be proc hir_create_map_literal from HIR

    Let child_count be proc ast_node_child_count from HCLParser with obj_node
    Let i be 0

    While i is less than child_count:
        Let child be proc ast_node_child from HCLParser with obj_node, i
        Let child_type be proc ast_node_type from HCLParser with child

        If child_type is equal to HCLParser.HCL_ATTRIBUTE:
            Let key be proc ast_node_value from HCLParser with child
            Let attr_child_count be proc ast_node_child_count from HCLParser with child

            If attr_child_count is greater than 0:
                Let value_node be proc ast_node_child from HCLParser with child, 0
                Let hir_value be proc translate_expression with ctx, value_node

                Let hir_key be proc hir_create_string_literal from HIR with key
                proc hir_add_map_entry from HIR with hir_object, hir_key, hir_value
            End If
        End If

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Return hir_object
End Process

@Reasoning:
HCL binary operators (arithmetic, comparison, logical) need to be remapped from HCL's textual representation to HIR's enumerated HIR_OP_* constants. Translating operands first keeps the HIR construction call atomic at the end.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Validates that binary_node has at least 2 children, translates both operands recursively, maps the operator string to HIR_OP_* via map_hcl_operator_to_hir, then creates a HIR binary expression. Returns 0 for malformed nodes with fewer than two children.
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_binary_expr" takes ctx as Integer, binary_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let operator be proc ast_node_value from HCLParser with binary_node
    Let child_count be proc ast_node_child_count from HCLParser with binary_node

    If child_count is less than 2:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let left_node be proc ast_node_child from HCLParser with binary_node, 0
    Let right_node be proc ast_node_child from HCLParser with binary_node, 1

    Let hir_left be proc translate_expression with ctx, left_node
    Let hir_right be proc translate_expression with ctx, right_node

    Let hir_op be proc map_hcl_operator_to_hir with operator

    Return proc hir_create_binary_expr from HIR with hir_op, hir_left, hir_right
End Process

@Reasoning:
A single point of truth for HCL-to-HIR operator translation prevents drift between the various expression translators that need it. Falling back to HIR_OP_ADD on unknown operators is a deliberate non-throwing choice — HIR validation will catch genuinely invalid expressions later.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Linear sequence of string_equals tests against each supported operator token ("+", "-", "*", "/", "==", "!=", "<", "<=", ">", ">=", "&&", "||"), returning the matching HIR_OP_* constant on the first hit. Returns HIR_OP_ADD as a default when nothing matches.
@End Implementation

Process called "map_hcl_operator_to_hir" takes operator as Integer returns Integer:
    Let is_plus be proc string_equals from StringCore with operator, "+"
    If is_plus is equal to 1:
        Return HIR.HIR_OP_ADD
    End If

    Let is_minus be proc string_equals from StringCore with operator, "-"
    If is_minus is equal to 1:
        Return HIR.HIR_OP_SUBTRACT
    End If

    Let is_star be proc string_equals from StringCore with operator, "*"
    If is_star is equal to 1:
        Return HIR.HIR_OP_MULTIPLY
    End If

    Let is_slash be proc string_equals from StringCore with operator, "/"
    If is_slash is equal to 1:
        Return HIR.HIR_OP_DIVIDE
    End If

    Let is_eq be proc string_equals from StringCore with operator, "=="
    If is_eq is equal to 1:
        Return HIR.HIR_OP_EQUAL
    End If

    Let is_neq be proc string_equals from StringCore with operator, "!="
    If is_neq is equal to 1:
        Return HIR.HIR_OP_NOT_EQUAL
    End If

    Let is_lt be proc string_equals from StringCore with operator, "<"
    If is_lt is equal to 1:
        Return HIR.HIR_OP_LESS_THAN
    End If

    Let is_le be proc string_equals from StringCore with operator, "<="
    If is_le is equal to 1:
        Return HIR.HIR_OP_LESS_EQUAL
    End If

    Let is_gt be proc string_equals from StringCore with operator, ">"
    If is_gt is equal to 1:
        Return HIR.HIR_OP_GREATER_THAN
    End If

    Let is_ge be proc string_equals from StringCore with operator, ">="
    If is_ge is equal to 1:
        Return HIR.HIR_OP_GREATER_EQUAL
    End If

    Let is_and be proc string_equals from StringCore with operator, "&&"
    If is_and is equal to 1:
        Return HIR.HIR_OP_LOGICAL_AND
    End If

    Let is_or be proc string_equals from StringCore with operator, "||"
    If is_or is equal to 1:
        Return HIR.HIR_OP_LOGICAL_OR
    End If

    Return HIR.HIR_OP_ADD
End Process

@Reasoning:
HCL unary operators are limited to logical-not ("!") and arithmetic negation ("-"). Translating the operand once and then branching on operator avoids duplicating recursion in each operator arm.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Validates child_count >= 1, translates the single operand, then dispatches on operator: "!" -> HIR_OP_LOGICAL_NOT, "-" -> HIR_OP_NEGATE, default -> return operand unchanged (safe identity for unknown unary).
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_unary_expr" takes ctx as Integer, unary_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let operator be proc ast_node_value from HCLParser with unary_node
    Let child_count be proc ast_node_child_count from HCLParser with unary_node

    If child_count is less than 1:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let operand_node be proc ast_node_child from HCLParser with unary_node, 0
    Let hir_operand be proc translate_expression with ctx, operand_node

    Let is_not be proc string_equals from StringCore with operator, "!"
    If is_not is equal to 1:
        Return proc hir_create_unary_expr from HIR with HIR.HIR_OP_LOGICAL_NOT, hir_operand
    End If

    Let is_minus be proc string_equals from StringCore with operator, "-"
    If is_minus is equal to 1:
        Return proc hir_create_unary_expr from HIR with HIR.HIR_OP_NEGATE, hir_operand
    End If

    Return hir_operand
End Process

@Reasoning:
HCL ternary expressions ("cond ? a : b") are stored as three child nodes; HIR has a dedicated conditional expression that maps one-to-one, so translation is just three sub-translations and a constructor call.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Validates at least three children, translates condition/true-branch/false-branch in order via translate_expression, then constructs an HIR conditional expression. Returns 0 on malformed nodes.
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_conditional" takes ctx as Integer, cond_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let child_count be proc ast_node_child_count from HCLParser with cond_node

    If child_count is less than 3:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let condition_node be proc ast_node_child from HCLParser with cond_node, 0
    Let true_node be proc ast_node_child from HCLParser with cond_node, 1
    Let false_node be proc ast_node_child from HCLParser with cond_node, 2

    Let hir_condition be proc translate_expression with ctx, condition_node
    Let hir_true be proc translate_expression with ctx, true_node
    Let hir_false be proc translate_expression with ctx, false_node

    Return proc hir_create_ternary_expr from HIR with hir_condition, hir_true, hir_false
End Process

@Reasoning:
HCL function calls store the callee as the first child and arguments as subsequent children. A bare-identifier callee (format, join, lookup, ...) becomes a HIR identifier; any other callee form (namespaced or member-access callee) is translated through the general expression lowering so every callee shape produces a faithful HIR callee node. Arguments are translated and appended in source order.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Validates at least one child (the callee). If the callee child is HCL_IDENTIFIER, builds a HIR identifier from its name; otherwise lowers the callee child via translate_expression so member/namespaced callees survive. Wraps the callee in a call expression, then iterates the remaining children (index 1..n) translating each as an argument and appending via hir_add_argument.
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_function_call" takes ctx as Integer, call_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let child_count be proc ast_node_child_count from HCLParser with call_node

    If child_count is less than 1:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let func_node be proc ast_node_child from HCLParser with call_node, 0
    Let func_name_node be proc ast_node_type from HCLParser with func_node

    Let hir_callee be 0
    If func_name_node is equal to HCLParser.HCL_IDENTIFIER:
        Let func_name be proc ast_node_value from HCLParser with func_node
        Set hir_callee to proc hir_create_identifier from HIR with func_name
    Otherwise:
        Set hir_callee to proc translate_expression with ctx, func_node
    End If

    Let hir_call be proc hir_create_call_expr from HIR with hir_callee

    Let i be 1
    While i is less than child_count:
        Let arg_node be proc ast_node_child from HCLParser with call_node, i
        Let hir_arg be proc translate_expression with ctx, arg_node
        proc hir_add_argument from HIR with hir_call, hir_arg
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Return hir_call
End Process

@Reasoning:
HCL member access ("a.b") splits into an object expression and an identifier-shaped member name. The translator only reads the name from identifier-typed second children to avoid producing garbled HIR if the parser ever yields a non-identifier member.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Validates at least two children, translates the object subexpression, then reads the second child's type and extracts its value only when it is HCL_IDENTIFIER. Builds an HIR member expression with the translated object and the member name string.
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_member_expr" takes ctx as Integer, member_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let child_count be proc ast_node_child_count from HCLParser with member_node

    If child_count is less than 2:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let object_node be proc ast_node_child from HCLParser with member_node, 0
    Let member_name_node be proc ast_node_child from HCLParser with member_node, 1

    Let hir_object be proc translate_expression with ctx, object_node

    Let member_name be ""
    Let member_type be proc ast_node_type from HCLParser with member_name_node
    If member_type is equal to HCLParser.HCL_IDENTIFIER:
        Set member_name to proc ast_node_value from HCLParser with member_name_node
    End If

    Return proc hir_create_member_expr from HIR with hir_object, member_name
End Process

@Reasoning:
HCL index access ("a[i]") translates to HIR index expressions. Both the object and the index can be arbitrary expressions (the index can be a string for map access or a number for list access), so both are translated through the general translate_expression dispatcher.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Validates at least two children, translates object and index sub-expressions, then constructs an HIR index expression with both.
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_index_expr" takes ctx as Integer, index_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let child_count be proc ast_node_child_count from HCLParser with index_node

    If child_count is less than 2:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let object_node be proc ast_node_child from HCLParser with index_node, 0
    Let index_expr_node be proc ast_node_child from HCLParser with index_node, 1

    Let hir_object be proc translate_expression with ctx, object_node
    Let hir_index be proc translate_expression with ctx, index_expr_node

    Return proc hir_create_index_expr from HIR with hir_object, hir_index
End Process

@Reasoning:
HCL splat ("a.*.b") has no direct HIR equivalent because HIR member expressions don't model wildcard projection. Representing it as a member expression with name "*" plus an "hcl_splat" metadata flag lets later passes recognise and expand it.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Validates at least one child, translates the object subexpression, builds an HIR member expression with "*" as the member name, then stamps the result with "hcl_splat"=1 metadata before returning.
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_splat_expr" takes ctx as Integer, splat_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let child_count be proc ast_node_child_count from HCLParser with splat_node

    If child_count is less than 1:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let object_node be proc ast_node_child from HCLParser with splat_node, 0
    Let hir_object be proc translate_expression with ctx, object_node

    Note: Create splat as special HIR construct with metadata
    Let hir_splat be proc hir_create_member_expr from HIR with hir_object, "*"
    proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_splat, "hcl_splat", 1

    Return hir_splat
End Process

@Reasoning:
HCL for-expressions ("for v in xs : transform(v)") are comprehensions, not statements. HIR's for-expression construct accepts a sequence of "components" (iterator var, source, body, optional filter, optional key); the translator simply forwards each AST child as a component and tags the result with "hcl_for_expr"=1 metadata so the eventual emitter knows the source semantics.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Creates an empty HIR for-expression, stamps the metadata flag, iterates all for_node children, translates each as a generic expression via translate_expression, and appends through hir_add_for_component preserving source order.
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_for_expr" takes ctx as Integer, for_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let child_count be proc ast_node_child_count from HCLParser with for_node

    Note: HCL for-expression children (no map key): [var IDENTIFIER, collection, transform].
    Note: We map to a HIR for-in node whose variable holds the iterator name, iterable holds
    Note: the collection expression, and body holds the transform expression. The hcl_for_expr
    Note: metadata flag tells the backend to re-emit comprehension syntax rather than a loop.
    Let hir_for be proc hir_create_for_in from HIR
    proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_for, "hcl_for_expr", 1

    If child_count is less than 3:
        Return hir_for
    End If

    Let var_node be proc ast_node_child from HCLParser with for_node, 0
    Let var_name be proc ast_node_value from HCLParser with var_node
    proc hir_set_for_in_variable from HIR with hir_for, var_name

    Note: When a map key variable is present there are 4 children
    Note: [val_var, key_var, collection, transform]; otherwise 3.
    Let collection_index be 1
    Let transform_index be 2
    If child_count is greater than 3:
        Set collection_index to 2
        Set transform_index to 3
    End If

    Let collection_node be proc ast_node_child from HCLParser with for_node, collection_index
    Let hir_collection be proc translate_expression with ctx, collection_node
    proc hir_set_for_in_iterable from HIR with hir_for, hir_collection

    Let transform_node be proc ast_node_child from HCLParser with for_node, transform_index
    Let hir_transform be proc translate_expression with ctx, transform_node
    proc hir_set_for_in_body from HIR with hir_for, hir_transform

    Return hir_for
End Process

Note: ===================================================================
Note: PUBLIC API
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
The public API name uses the "<frontend>_to_hir_translate" convention that the universal translation framework expects when wiring frontends together. Exposing this thin alias decouples the internal naming (translate_hcl_to_hir) from the framework contract.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Single-line delegation to translate_hcl_to_hir.
@End Implementation

Process called "hcl_to_hir_translate" takes hcl_ast as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc translate_hcl_to_hir with hcl_ast
End Process

@Reasoning:
Public single-arg facade invoked by the translation dispatcher's
LANG_HCL arm. Wires the full source -> HIR pipeline: HCLLexer
create_hcl_lexer + tokenize produce a token list, HCLParser
create_hcl_parser wraps it, parse_hcl_configuration walks tokens
into the configuration AST root, and translate_hcl_to_hir lowers
the AST into HIR.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
lexer = HCLLexer.create_hcl_lexer(source); tokens = HCLLexer.tokenize(lexer);
parser = HCLParser.create_hcl_parser(tokens); ast = HCLParser.parse_hcl_configuration(parser);
return translate_hcl_to_hir(ast). Short-circuit on ast == 0.
@End Implementation

Process called "hcl_to_hir_from_source" takes source_code as Integer returns Integer:
    Let lexer be proc create_hcl_lexer from HCLLexer with source_code
    Let tokens be proc tokenize from HCLLexer with lexer
    Let parser be proc create_hcl_parser from HCLParser with tokens
    Let ast be proc parse_hcl_configuration from HCLParser with parser
    If ast is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc translate_hcl_to_hir with ast
End Process
